WITH ElementCombinations AS (
    SELECT a1.element AS element1, a2.element AS element2, COUNT(*) AS combination_count
    FROM connected c
    JOIN atom a1 ON c.atom_id = a1.atom_id
    JOIN atom a2 ON c.atom_id2 = a2.atom_id
    GROUP BY a1.element, a2.element
),
MostCommonCombination AS (
    SELECT element1, element2, MAX(combination_count) AS max_count
    FROM ElementCombinations
    GROUP BY element1, element2
    ORDER BY max_count DESC
    LIMIT 1
),
TotalBonds AS (
    SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_count

)

FROM MostCommonCombination mcc, TotalBonds tb;	----- bird -----	toxicology

    p1.publisher_name AS publisher_with_more_superheroes,
    ABS(COUNT(s1.id) - COUNT(s2.id)) AS difference
FROM 
    publisher p1
JOIN 
    superhero s1 ON p1.id = s1.publisher_id
LEFT JOIN 
    publisher p2 ON p2.publisher_name IN ('DC Comics', 'Marvel Comics') AND p2.id != p1.id
LEFT JOIN 
    superhero s2 ON p2.id = s2.publisher_id
WHERE 
    p1.publisher_name IN ('DC Comics', 'Marvel Comics')
GROUP BY 
    p1.publisher_name
ORDER BY 
    COUNT(s1.id) DESC
LIMIT 1;	----- bird -----	superhero

1481:
WITH AnnualConsumption AS (
    SELECT 
        c."Segment",
        y."CustomerID",
        SUM(y."Consumption") AS TotalConsumption
    FROM 
        yearmonth y
    JOIN 
        customers c ON y."CustomerID" = c."CustomerID"
    WHERE 
        y."Date" LIKE '2013%' AND c."Currency" = 'CZK'
    GROUP BY 
        c."Segment", y."CustomerID"
),
MinConsumption AS (
    SELECT 
        "Segment",
        MIN(TotalConsumption) AS MinTotalConsumption
    FROM 
        AnnualConsumption
    GROUP BY 
        "Segment"
),
AverageConsumption AS (
    SELECT 
        "Segment",
        AVG(TotalConsumption) AS AvgConsumption
    FROM 
        AnnualConsumption
    WHERE 
        TotalConsumption IN (SELECT MinTotalConsumption FROM MinConsumption)
    GROUP BY 
        "Segment"
)
SELECT 
    a1."Segment" AS Segment1,
    a2."Segment" AS Segment2,
    ABS(a1.AvgConsumption - a2.AvgConsumption) AS ConsumptionDifference
FROM 
    AverageConsumption a1
JOIN 
    AverageConsumption a2 ON a1."Segment" < a2."Segment"
WHERE 
    (a1."Segment" = 'SME' AND a2."Segment" = 'LAM') OR
    (a1."Segment" = 'LAM' AND a2."Segment" = 'KAM') OR
    (a1."Segment" = 'KAM' AND a2."Segment" = 'SME');	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
1482:
SELECT Segment, 
       (SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(Date, 1, 4) = '2013' THEN Consumption ELSE 0 END) - 
        SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(Date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN Consumption ELSE 0 END)) / 
        NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(Date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN Consumption ELSE 0 END), 0) * 100 AS PercentageIncrease
FROM yearmonth ym
JOIN customers c ON ym.CustomerID = c.CustomerID
WHERE c.Currency = 'EUR' AND c.Segment IN ('SME', 'LAM', 'KAM')
GROUP BY Segment
ORDER BY PercentageIncrease DESC;	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing

WITH customer_payment AS (
    SELECT "CustomerID"
    FROM transactions_1k
    WHERE "Price" = 634.8 AND "Date" = '2012-08-25'
),
consumption_2012 AS (
    SELECT "CustomerID", SUM("Consumption") AS total_2012
    FROM yearmonth
    WHERE "Date" LIKE '2012%' AND "CustomerID" IN (SELECT "CustomerID" FROM customer_payment)
    GROUP BY "CustomerID"
),
consumption_2013 AS (
    SELECT "CustomerID", SUM("Consumption") AS total_2013
    FROM yearmonth
    WHERE "Date" LIKE '2013%' AND "CustomerID" IN (SELECT "CustomerID" FROM customer_payment)
    GROUP BY "CustomerID"
)
SELECT c2012."CustomerID", 
       ((c2012.total_2012 - c2013.total_2013) / c2012.total_2012) * 100 AS decrease_rate
FROM consumption_2012 c2012
JOIN consumption_2013 c2013 ON c2012."CustomerID" = c2013."CustomerID";	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
